When it comes to the segmentation of the market by voltage, low voltage circuit breakers are projected to witness significant demand in 2029. This uptrend can be attributed to the escalating need for small-scale applications in the residential sector, where low voltage systems play a crucial role in ensuring the safe and reliable distribution of electricity. As more residential construction projects and smart home installations take place, the demand for low voltage circuit breakers is expected to surge, further driving market growth and expansion in this segment.

